Systems development life cycle (SDLC): describes typical progression between phases
- Initiation: identifying opportunity
- Planning: allocating resources
- Requirements: understanding needs
- Design: planning solution
- Implementation: creating solution
- Testing: accepting solution
- Deployment: delivering solution
- Maintenance: supporting solution

Agile software development
DevOps: development and operations workflow automation
Microservices: loosely coupled services, communication via lightweight protocols, independent deployment
- cons: complexity, new interfaces, network communication
- pros: modularity, scalability, allows mix of technologies
